H3.text: who died doing the luge in the olympics. Nodar Kumaritashvili

A4.text: Nodar Kumaritashvili died during a training run for the 2010 Winter Olympics in Whistler, British Columbia, Canada.

A5.text: Kumaritashvili became the fourth athlete to die during preparations for a Winter Olympics, after British luger Kazimierz Kay-Skrzypecki and Australian skier Ross Milne (both 1964 Innsbruck), and Swiss speed skier Nicolas Bochatay (1992 Albertville).
